crime_tv.title: Crime TV
crime_tv.description: An action-packed mix of scripted whodunits and shocking, real-life murder mysteries ripped from today's headlines.

0300005738.title: Murphy's Law
0300005738.description: Detective Sergeant Tommy Murphy is an undercover cop with a troubled history and ties to a crime boss. Will his past interfere with his work?

0300005307.title: Crime Files With David Wilson
0300005307.description: From double lives to how crimes of passion occur, an expert criminologist uses proven techniques and psychology to explain various crime themes.

0300010347.title: People Magazine Investigates: Crimes of Fashion

0300010104.title: LA's Finest

0300004774.title: Dr. G: Medical Examiner

0300005731.title: Crownies

0300006444.title: Murder on the Internet

0300004985.title: Midsomer Murders

0300005571.title: Catch Me Now

0300006625.title: Charlie's Angels

0300010317.title: Southern Fried Homicide

04490.title: Hunted UK
04490.description: If you had to disappear tomorrow with some of the world’s best-missing persons experts looking for you and the most cutting edge technology keeping tabs on your electronic footprint, could you just vanish? To find out, 14 ordinary Brits from a cross-section of British society become fugitives and go on the run. With just £450 in the bank, they must evade capture for 28 days. Hunting them down are some of the world’s best investigators selected from law enforcement, military intelligence, cyber analysis, online profiling, and human tracking. In charge of them is Brett Lovegrove, former Head of Counter-Terrorism for the City of London Police who led the City of London Police response to the 7/7 bombings and the foiled attacks two weeks later. HUNTED is a real manhunt, a game of cat-and-mouse, captured 24 hours a day over four weeks, with full access to both sides of the pursuit, in order to make the first ever factual-thriller on British television.

0300009854.title: Heartland Homicide

0300010186.description: Discover the stories behind what made and shaped the most notorious figures in Australian criminal history.

04149.title: World's Most Evil Killers
04149.description: Criminologists, forensic pathologists, federal agents and other experts delve into the lives of the most terrifying and notorious killers in history.

0300007006.title: New Scotland Yard Files
0300007006.description: Hear from some of the most determined detectives in Scotland Yard as they open their files to share exactly how they caught notorious killers.

04357.title: Nurses Who Kill
04357.description: This series takes a horrifyingly close look at hospitals and nursing homes, to uncover how nurses have gotten away with actual murder.

0300005072.title: Kavanagh QC
0300005072.description: Meet the gruff but always fair barrister Kavanagh who fights for justice for the innocent by day and battles a turbulent family life by night.

0300010222.title: A Crime to Remember
0300010222.description: Fashions may change, but these crimes of the past never go out of style. This series looks back at popular murder cases from the ‘50s and '60s.

0769.title: Secret Agent
0769.description: Patrick McGoohan stars as John Drake in Secret Agent, the popular television series from the Golden Age of Spy Thrillers, the 1960s.

0300010081.title: Nikita
0300010081.description: Betrayed by the secret government agency that made her an assassin, the charming and deadly Nikita makes it her mission to undermine the organization.

03582.title: O.J. Speaks: The Hidden Tapes
03582.description: Offering unique access to the civil trial of O.J. Simpson, this special features rare deposition tapes and interviews with the family of Ron Goldman.

0300006850.title: Cheating Vegas
0300006850.description: Interviews and security camera footage expose foul play at casinos, from high-tech hacking, to daring inside jobs, to complex criminal conspiracies

0300009914.title: Airport Strikers
0300009914.description: A special police force responsible for maintaining airport safety encounters different situations on duty and sees life's joys and sorrow.

0300008551.title: Sue Thomas: F.B.Eye
0300008551.description: Inspired by a true story, a deaf woman uses her lip-reading skills and trusty dog to help an FBI surveillance team bring bad guys to justice.

0300010331.title: Ted Bundy: Mind of a Monster
0300010331.description: This show gives viewers exclusive access and unique insights into the mind of one of the most infamous serial killers in American history, Ted Bundy.

0300008242.title: Serial Psyche
0300008242.description: What makes a serial killer go on a deadly spree? This docuseries examines the psychological underpinnings that frame their decisions.

0300004771.title: Skeleton Stories
0300004771.description: Real-life cases of crime victims whose discovered remains reveal the secrets and cause of death, as explained and investigated by forensic experts.

0300007227.title: No Go Zones: The World's Toughest Places
0300007227.description: This series reveals what it really means to be part of some of the world's most infamous microcosms. At each location, walk and talk with the people who are part of these communities, who dance with danger every day. Prostitutes, drug dealers, gang member, and police all face different challenges in the same struggle: stay alive or die trying.

01502.title: Brothers in Arms
01502.description: Bikie Wars: Brothers in Arms tells the true story of two motorcycle clubs, and two men, on a journey from loyalty to rivalry with deadly consequence. On September 2nd, Fathers Day 1984, two motorcycle clubs the Bandidos and the Comancheros went to war at a public swap meet. After a brief but violent battle, seven people had been shot dead, including a young innocent bystander, and some forty other club members needed hospitalisation. Bikie Wars: Brothers in Arms is the story of how that day came to pass.

0300006517.title: FBI: Critical Incident
0300006517.description: The real-life stories of the FBI’s Critical Incident division who help local and state law agencies handle high-stakes and crucial crimes in-progress.

0300007019.title: Claimed and Shamed
0300007019.description: A crack team of insurance investigators confront a growing UK epidemic, as they sniff out and hunt down suspected fraudsters, in this dynamic series.

0300005055.title: Case Histories
0300005055.description: Haunted by his own violent and traumatic past, a former soldier puts his considerable skills to good use as a crusading private investigator.

0300010309.title: Swamp Murders
0300010309.description: This series reveals the salacious stories behind bodies found in swamps. Featuring reenactments and interviews with people involved in each case.

0300000094.title: Blood, Lies and Alibis
0300000094.description: The show follows criminal investigators as they uncover the stories behind brutal killings and deliver justice to families mourning their dead

0300009326.title: Señorita Pólvora
0300009326.description: La historia de una mujer bella que se enamora de un sicario. Sin embargo, descubre que su querido pertenece a uno de los cárteles más poderosos.

01751.title: Blood and Water
01751.description: Jo has just been assigned her first big murder case as Lead Detective, right after receiving the worst news of her life. Now she must put aside the personal while taking on the wealthy Xie family.

02181.title: Blue Heelers
02181.description: The series primarily focuses on the daily lives of Victorian police officers working at a police station in the fictional small town of Mount Thomas.

04043.title: Crimes That Shook Australia

0300010209.title: Spenser: For Hire

0300009727.title: AI Cappuccino

0300004912.title: True CSI
0300004912.description: Examine and solve a murder with the suspense of whodunit and the visceral punch of fly on the wall realism.

0300009827.title: Squad 38

0300009949.title: The Moment of Proof

0300009913.title: Armed Reaction 2021

02162.title: Kidnap & Ransom
02162.description: Dominic King is the best international hostage negotiator in the business. If only his home life were as satisfying as his professional.

0300009024.title: Law & Order True Crime: The Menendez Murders
0300009024.description: This gripping true-crime chapter of the franchise explores the notorious, nationally televised case of the Menendez brothers’ murder of their parents.

0300005736.title: Hamish MacBeth

0300005257.title: Border Security: Australia's Front Line

0300006776.title: Jeffrey Dahmer: Killer Cannibal

0300010102.title: La Femme Nikita
0300010102.description: Condemned to death for a vicious crime she didn't commit, Nikita reluctantly chooses to live as an assassin for a secret government agency.

0300007629.title: Meet, Marry, Murder

0300006079.title: Misterios Sin Revolver
0300006079.description: Entrevistas y recreaciones de crímenes, historias inexplicables y hasta sucesos paranormales que son incógnitas en los expedientes de investigadores.
